## Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for the LemonDrop Next.js project.

### Changes Made

**Modified:**
- `app/layout.js` - Added the `<Analytics />` component inside the body tag

### Implementation Details

1. **Framework Identification**: Confirmed this is a Next.js 16.2.1 project using the App Router pattern.

2. **Package Status**: The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already present in package.json but not properly configured.

3. **Configuration**: 
   - The Analytics import from `@vercel/analytics/next` was already present in the layout.js file
   - Added the `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the children component
   - This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router applications

4. **Verification**:
   - Build completed successfully with no errors
   - Linter check on layout.js passed with no issues
   - No breaking changes introduced to existing functionality

### Next Steps

To enable analytics tracking:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in your Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
3. Analytics data will automatically begin collecting after deployment

### Technical Notes

- Implementation follows the latest Vercel Analytics quickstart guide (fetched from official docs)
- Analytics component is placed at the end of the body tag for optimal page load performance
- No additional configuration files or environment variables are required
